                                    <p><font size="5">
                                        <b> The 16th International Symposium of the Tunisian Marketing Association (ATMC16)</b> will be an opportunity for participants to present their research and will provide a framework for fruitful scientific exchanges between academics and professionals. The symposium will be organized on <b> 06 and 07 April 2018 </b> by the Laboratory Enterprise and Research in Marketing (ERMA) of the Faculty of Economics and Management of Tunis (FSEGT). You are a novice or confirmed researcher and you want to share your thoughts with the scientific community, you will be offered the opportunity to present your contribution at this symposium.
                                    </p></font>			


                                    <h1 id="theme" class="title" style="background : rgba(255, 143, 0, 0.24) ;"><font color="#212358"><b><i>1.</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;THE THEME OF THE CONFERENCE</b></font></h1><br> 


                                    <p><font size="5"><b>The 16th ATM Symposium will be organized around the theme of "MARKETING AND CULTURE".</b> Culture is the whole of social production. It is far from being frozen. It is renewed, specializes and recomposes permanently. The relationship between culture and consumer behavior has been studied for a long time by marketing researchers. This facet of consumer behavior remains highly valued by researchers. Family, acculturation, religiosity, etc., are the main dimensions of culture. The aspects related to religiosity have been of particular interest to marketers in the last few years. ATMC16 will be open to professionals and researchers in the marketing of Islamic products and services and will be an opportunity for exchanges, sharing of experiences and reflection . It will also be an opportunity to discover innovative and original marketing issues and to discuss new trends in this field.

                                        </font></p>

                                    <h1 id="table" class="title" style="background : rgba(255, 143, 0, 0.24) ;"><font color="#212358"><b><i>2.</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;THE ROUND TABLE</b></font></h1><br> 

                                    <p><font size="5">A panel discussion will take place in the afternoon of the first day of the symposium. It will focus on <b> "The marketing of Islamic services" </b>. This debate will bring together professionals, civil society representatives, researchers and ATMC16 participants to discuss the theme. This debate will discuss the importance and prospects of development of Islamic products and services in Tunisia and around the world. Eventually, leaders of the three Islamic banks, the three Islamic insurers and the Islamic microfinance company will be actively present in the round table </font></p>

