                                    <h1 id="evaluation" class="title" style="background : rgba(255, 143, 0, 0.24) ;"><font color="#212358"><b><i>7.</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Evaluation of Communications </b></font></h1><br>

                                    <p><font size="5">The submitted manuscripts will be subject to an anonymous evaluation process by <b> two evaluators </b>. Accepted papers will be grouped into homogeneous themes and presented in sessions chaired by sessions. In case the two opinions diverge (acceptance + refusal), the paper will be evaluated by a third reader.  </font></p>

                                    <h1 id="prix" class="title"  style="background : rgba(255, 143, 0, 0.24) ;"><font color="#212358"><b><i>8.</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Awards and publications of the best papers</b></font></h1><br> 

                                    <p><font size="5"><b>1.&nbsp;Prizes and publications of the best papers:</b>The scientific committee will award prizes for the best papers related to the specific themes of <b>the ATMC16:</b><br>
                                        <b>1.1.</b>&nbsp;<b>The Laamouri Institute</b> price will be awarded to the best communication on the basis of the originality of the issue addressed and the rigorous design of the research carried out.<br>
                                        <b>1.2.</b>&nbsp; <b>The Sphinx</b> price will be awarded to the best communication on <b>the basis of the qualitative and quantitative methodology followed.</b><br>
                                        The prizes will be distributed at the closing ceremony.<br>
                                        <b>2.&nbsp; best paper publications:</b> <b>The International Journal of Islamic Marketing and Branding </b> will be awarded for the best paper on Islamic marketing. The eight best accepted papers, written in English and dealing with the topic of Islamic marketing, will be published in a special issue of the newspaper which will be published in December 2018<br>
