                                    <h1 id="GUIDELINE" class="title" style="background : rgba(255, 143, 0, 0.24) ;"><font color="#212358"><b><i>10.</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;"The ATMC GUIDELINE" submission  </b></font></h1><br>

                                    <p><font size="5">Submissions must comply with the following: <br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp;<b>Writing can be done in French, English or Arabic</b><br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp;<b> The text of the communication contains a maximum of</b> <font color="red"> 12 pages</font> (not including the bibliography and annexes) <br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp;<b>The researcher must submit two files on the site www.colloque-ATM.com</b><br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-file-text"> </i> &nbsp;<b> File 1. Cover letter:</b> lthe title, the name of the author (s), their functions, contact details and e-mail addresses. This page will be detached in order to make the evaluation anonymous<br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-file-text"> </i> &nbsp;	<b>File 2. Manuscript:</b>the title, a summary of 50 words maximum (single spacing) and 5 key words. The title, abstract and keywords must be written in English and French.<br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp;File in Word format, mandatory<br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp; Font: <b>CAMBRIA</b>, size 12 <br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp;2.5 cm margins on all four sides <br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp; Interlining 1.5<br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp;No header, no footer, <br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp; Pagination bottom right<br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp;Tables and figures (numbered) are inserted in the text in the appropriate place.
                                        <br>Indicate their sources. <br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp;Insert the bibliography and annexes at the end of the text.<br> 
                                        <i class="fa fa-angle-double-right"> </i> &nbsp;<b>The bibliography must be presented according to APA standards as follows:</b> <br> 
                                        <i class="fa fa-hand-o-right"> </i> &nbsp; <b>Journal articles:</b> Name of the author followed by the initial of the first name (year), Full title of the article, title of the journal in italics, volume, number, page number. <br>
                                        <b><font color="red">Example:</font>Bagozzi R.P. et Yi Y. (1988), On the evaluation of structural equation models, Journal of the Academy of Marketing Science, 16(1), 74-94.</b><br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-hand-o-right"> </i> &nbsp;	<b> Works:</b> Name of the author followed by the initial of the first name (year), Full title of the work in italics, place of publication, name of the publisher. <br>
                                        <b><font color="red">Example :</font> Brochand B. et Lendrevie J., (2001), le Publicitor,Dalloz : Paris. 755 pages.</b><br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-hand-o-right"> </i> &nbsp;	<b>Proceedings of symposiums and colloquium:</b> Name of the author followed by the initial of the first name (year), Title of the communication, the title of the colloquium in italics, volume, place of the colloquium, page number.<br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-hand-o-right"> </i> &nbsp;	<b>Unpublished documents:</b> (nature of the document: thesis, research report, report ...): Name of the author followed by the initial of the first name (year), Full title of document, Nature of document, name of university or Of the school, place of reference. <br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-hand-o-right"> </i> &nbsp;<b>	  For a data taken from the internet: </b> Concerning Internet citations, the only mention of the site is not enough. It is also necessary to specify who is the author and / or institution (university, consulting firm, organization, ministry) and also specify the date of consultation<br>
                                        <i class="fa fa-hand-o-right"> </i> &nbsp;<b><font color="red">	Example :</font> GOUGEON, P., 2004, « The European Enterprise: Managing Cultural Diversity », <br>Les Échos, dans http://www.lesechos.fr/formations/entreprise_globale/articles/article_12_4.htm,  accessed on 3 March 2014.</b><br>
                                        <br>
                                        <b>IMPORTANT NOTE: Papers that do not comply with the instructions of the<font color="red"> "ATMC </font> GUIDELINE" indicated, will not be accepted by the reading committee.</font></b><br>
                                        </font></p>


